															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/name" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(254716); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=254716&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204484" alt="name" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=254716)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/name" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(254716); return false;" >name</a></span> <span class="odate time_1237659724 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Mar 2009 18:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-424407">
									

<p>I came up with the outline for the plot a while ago, and knew i would have to alter the mechanics of memory erasing for this to work, but i only really decided to add focus on that part of it when i read a tv tropes description on our page named "Laser Guided Amnesics" which is a troup about fictional memory erasers that work easily and efficient, in one second, without any problem, and i guess i wanted to, in their terminology, subvert it.</p>
<p>So the subversion is in this tale and if its liked it could become "official". I think it would make a good addition to canon, because it just adds another layer of lies and secrecy to the foundation, and makes them even darker and more ruthless.</p>

							</div>

								
