															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/yubi-shines" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(264675); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=264675&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204484" alt="Yubi Shines" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=264675)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/yubi-shines" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(264675); return false;" >Yubi Shines</a></span> <span class="odate time_1237680252 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 Mar 2009 00:04</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-424697">
									

<p>I'm not sold on it, honestly. Torture has gone out of fashion for a simple reason: It doesn't work. It's not clean or efficient or reliable. It's comparatively easy to break someone, but it's not easy to make sure the person is still going to be functional afterwards. As a method of extracting information, it's wretched, because they'll say anything just to make it stop, and "anything" isn't necessarily going to be the truth.</p>
<p>There's a case where a nun was kidnapped and tortured over 24 hours (among other things, she was made to kill another captive that she had bonded with), and as a result she lost all her memories. She remembers the torture in perfect detail, however, and that's not what Class A Amnesiacs are supposed to do.</p>
<p>(<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dianna_Ortiz">Wiki article.</a>)</p>
<p>If the Foundation was about being bloody little sadists, perhaps, but remember: TV Tropes has us down as "Necessarily Evil."</p>

							</div>

								
