			<div class="content" id="post-content-424731">
									

<p>you only saw a small part of the process. There were multiple facets briefly mentioned; drugging, mind games, electrocution,chemicals. Torture itself is inefficient, yes, but when psychological and physical torture is performed for the purpose of mental conditioning its relatively useful; brainwashing is comparatively easy to do because the response to it (submission) is ingrained in us. Consider Patty Hearst. She was kidnapped, and developed a completely new personality weeks later. Maybe i didn't make that clear enough, he wasn't just torturing them until they said, "ok, ok, its hurts so much i promise not to tell anyone" he was doing it until they couldn't form rational conclusions anymore, couldn't think or sleep, until they gave in out of pure exhaustion and became moldable. He reprogrammed them, something that is completely possible in the real world.</p>
<p>But you also briefly touched upon a point I was making. Its not reliable. Its a wretched method of doing anything. I meant it to come across like that. That's the whole point. you say its "gone out of fashion" Really? Well what do we have in its place? Hmmm. Its the best we can do… and what else do they have? Because Class A Amnesics are a lie. Consider it, if you were an overseer, wouldn't you make up something like that so most of The Foundation personnel would never have to realize exactly what needs to be done in order to protect their secrecy? And it probably turns out that most of the conditioning fails later, its only a temporary fix, and the Foundation has to hunt them down later, or just wait until their mind completely shatters. But how many people in The Foundation do you think would know this or want to know this?</p>
<p>And of course, it doesn't contradict anything, because Class A Amnesiac is a cover up, its doublespeak, and its inclusion in any article is paradigm manipulation. We have data expunged, of course other things are altered as well, and probably in a less noticeable way.</p>
<p>However just because the truth is different from what is perceived doesn't mean it has to be constantly alluded or mentioned; after all it is a deep dark secret.</p>
<p>(This is just my suggestion; i could simply put 1985 on the top as a date and say Class As started out as a lie, but then they eventually discovered the tech. still the same eerieness that there's secrets within the Foundation itself.)</p>

							</div>

								
