<p>name, you're basically taking it one step too far.</p>
<p>The Foundation does engage in torture, yes, but the method you describe is… sloppy. Why the hell would they use something as unreliable as torture, when a bullet to the head would be much more reliable and effective?</p>
<p>The reason that Class A Amnesiacs are even used is because they are MORE effective than simply eliminating the target. This implies a 100% success rate without any possibility that the tampering has been detected.</p>
<p>I like the story a lot, but I place it in Class B Canon: that is, to say, it could be true, but it seriously contradicts a lot of prior precedent: references to administering Class A Amnesiacs to 231-7 during Procedure 110-Montauk, for instance, or Dr. Rights' prior statements that her boyfriend has been drugged repeatedly using Class A Amnesiacs to cover up the evidence of her real job. Your theory could be true, but it would require a lot of finessing of canon.</p>

							</div>

								
					
