			<div class="content" id="post-content-425768">
									

<p>Well, you certainly succeeded witn that intention, at least from my point of view. I found the ending a trifle anticlimactic; I don't like to interfere with somebody else's story, but what I was hoping for and what I, personally, would have found disturbing, would be a Dr. Glut who came out of the experience a bit grimmer, a bit worse for wear, but willing to continue with the dark work so necessary for the world's continued function; an implication that this practice, horrible even to contemplate after one has first become familiar with the term "class A amnesiac", will continue, echoing the ongoing act of torture itself.</p>
<p>But that's just me! Needs a bit more grammatical polish, but it remains effective. It's good to see a bit of the terrifying side of our good Foundation. Too often it's just a big benign science place that pokes at curiosities.</p>

