														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-431041">
									

<p>I'm not sure this is an idea worth considering, but I'll throw it out there.</p>
<p>Considering how unlikely this interpretation of Class-A amnesiacs seems to be, according to several people… What if this is less an example of what the amnesiac is, so much as what happens if someone in charge of administrating it… breaks. In the head. And somehow goes unnoticed.</p>
<p>Perhaps him living in a town of his previous victims is just the Foundation's idea of punishment. Or maybe it's in his head. Either way, considering how many people- some of them important- in the foundation have likely received this amnesiac, I don't see how this story could be about a sane person.</p>
<p>Then again, I'm sick and have a headache, so make of this as you will.</p>

